<SUMMARY>
SUMMARY:

 The U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service (Service) gives notice that a public hearing will be held on the proposed determination
of endangered status for the Hine's emerald dragonfly (

Somatochlora hineana

) and that the comment period on the proposal will be reopened. The Hine's emerald dragonfly now persists in populations
in Cook, DuPage, and Will Counties in Illinois, and in Door County, Wisconsin. It occupies calcareous, marshy streams
associated with cattail marshes on dolomite bedrock. The public hearing and reopened comment period will allow comments
on this proposal to be submitted from all interested parties.

 
