Once the Secretary determines that a State failed to earmark the required amount of funds in the second fiscal year
preceding the fiscal year for which the State submits an application to administer the CIL program, the State would
be precluded from administering the CIL program in succeeding fiscal years. The Secretary believes that this proposed
