days after the center receives it or, if appealed to the Secretary, until the Secretary issues a final decision. 
Proposed  366.43 describes the minimum amount of information that the Secretary believes the final written
decision from the Director would have to contain to meet the statutory requirement of providing notice to the center
of the center's noncompliance with statutory requirements, including the reasons why the Director could not approve
