from 20 to 25 points and decreased the value of ``Likelihood of sustaining the program'' from 15 to 10 points in proposed
 367.22(b) and (h), respectively. 
Pursuant to proposed  367.23, the Secretary also would consider the geographic distribution of projects in
awarding these discretionary grants. The Secretary believes that it is important to have this program operate in
as many States as possible, and this proposed provision would give the Secretary the flexibility to accomplish this
purpose. 
Finally, proposed  367.41(a)(1) would incorporate section 752(g) of the Act that gives the designated State
agency discretion to operate or administer the OIB program or projects under Part 367 through grants to public or private
