(l) 

Conflict of interest. 

No member of the SILC is permitted to cast a vote on any matter that may provide direct financial benefit to the member
or the member's organization, that creates some other conflict of interest, or that otherwise gives the appearance
of a conflict of interest under State law, unless that member announces publicly to all members of the SILC and to the
public prior to his or her vote of the possible financial benefit, conflict of interest, or appearance of a conflict
of interest. 



